Package blackengine.rendering.pipeline.shaderPrograms.shaders.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DeadShaderReferenceException
    An instance of this exception type is thrown when a shader has been destroyed but is still called.
    NoSuchAttributeException
    An instance of this exception type is thrown when an attribute name was not found in the shader code, but still called from code.
    ShaderCompileException
    An instance of this exception type is thrown when a shader could not be compiled by OpenGL successfully.
    ShaderProgramAlreadyInitializedException
    An instance of this exception type is thrown when a shader program is initialized but had been initialized before already.
    ShaderProgramCompileException
    An instance of this exception type is thrown when a shader program did not get validated by OpenGL.
    UniformVariableNameNotFound
    An instance of this exception type is thrown when a uniform variable name is referenced but was not found on the shader source code.
